<subSubSection id="8AE5652AE97D4541FF17D739896CFC6C" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C24036A1E97D4541FF17D739896CFC6C" blockId="3.[156,768,523,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FF17D7398908FDA4" bold="true" box="[181,293,523,547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FE9DD73E89E7FDA3" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" box="[319,458,524,548]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
, body 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FDB4D73E8A8DFDA3" bold="true" box="[534,672,524,548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">more or less</emphasis>
divisible into physa, scapus, and 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE33D71E89C1FDC3" bold="true" box="[401,492,556,580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">scapulus</emphasis>
. Scapus and physa slightly differentiated from each other, the former with a thin epidermis without nemathybomes. No sphincter. Tentacles 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FF3ED7BC891FFD21" bold="true" box="[156,306,654,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">comparatively</emphasis>
short, the inner shorter than the 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FD24D7BC8AD2FD21" bold="true" box="[646,767,654,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">middle and</emphasis>
outer ones. 8 perfect and fertile mesenteries arranged as the macrocnemes in 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEFBD7FD89EFFD60" authorityName="Quatrefages" authorityYear="1842" box="[345,450,719,743]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" genus="Edwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FEFBD7FD89EFFD60" box="[345,450,719,743]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Edwardsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE77D7FD89C3FD60" bold="true" box="[469,494,719,743]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">16</emphasis>
microcnemes, 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FD3AD7FD89FCFC80" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">elongated from distal to proximal end</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE43D7DD8A22FCAF" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">The number distally is always equal or less than proximally</emphasis>
. Retractors of macrocnemes reniform to circumscribed. Parietal muscles distinct but weak. No nematosomes in the coelenteron. 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FD21D6638957FC2D" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
Cnidae; basitrich, spirocyst, microbasic 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE76D64389CCFC0E" bold="true" box="[468,481,881,905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">b</emphasis>
-mastigophore, and microbasic amastigophore
</emphasis>
(Revised from 
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FD86D6A08AE0FC2D" author="Carlgren, O." box="[548,717,914,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref5657" refString="Carlgren, O. 1949. A survey of the Ptychodactiaria, Corallimorpharia and Actiniaria. Kungliga Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar, Series 4 1: 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1949">Carlgren [1949]</bibRefCitation>
. Revised points are indicated in 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE67D68189D1FC4C" bold="true" box="[453,508,947,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">bold.</emphasis>
The diagnosis of cnidom is newly added).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8AE5652AE97D4541FF17D6C68AFAFB8B" box="[181,727,1011,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="C24036A1E97D4541FF17D6C68AFAFB8B" blockId="3.[156,768,523,2077]" box="[181,727,1011,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FF17D6C68912FB8C" bold="true" box="[181,319,1011,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
<typeStatus id="1D448803E97D4541FF17D6C688C4FB8B" box="[181,233,1012,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEFBD6C68AFEFB8B" authority="Uchida, 1932" authorityName="Uchida" authorityYear="1932" box="[345,723,1012,1036]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" genus="Milneedwardsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FEFBD6C68A6BFB8B" box="[345,582,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Milneedwardsia akkeshi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FDE9D6C68AFEFB8B" author="Uchida, T." box="[587,723,1012,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="571 - 575" refId="ref6464" refString="Uchida, T. 1932. On a new actinian, Milne-Edwardsia akkeshi n. sp., from northern Japan. Annotationes Zoologicae Japonenses 13: 571 - 575." type="journal article" year="1932">Uchida, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8AE5652AE97D4541FF17D1268D57FD60" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C24036A1E97D4541FF17D1268969F9F1" blockId="3.[156,768,523,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FF17D1268934FBAB" bold="true" box="[181,281,1044,1068]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Remarks.</emphasis>
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEDCD1268A27FBAB" authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1947" box="[382,522,1044,1068]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FEDCD1268A27FBAB" box="[382,522,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Metedwardsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established in 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FD78D1268924FBCA" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
because of its worm-like shape and eight macrocnemes to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FE1BD1678A85FBEA" authorityName="Uchida" authorityYear="1932" box="[441,680,1109,1133]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" genus="Milneedwardsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE1BD1678A85FBEA" box="[441,680,1109,1133]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Milneedwardsia akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because some morphological characters of this species did not correspond to the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FE16D1A48AD6FB29" authority="(Carlgren 1947)" baseAuthorityName="Carlgren" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[436,763,1174,1198]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" genus="Milneedwardsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE16D1A48A7FFB29" box="[436,594,1174,1198]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Milneedwardsia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FDFDD1A48AD8FB29" author="Carlgren, O." box="[607,757,1174,1198]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="90 - 106" refId="ref5628" refString="Carlgren, O. 1947. Further contributions to a revision of the Actiniaria and Corallimorpharia. Kungliga Fysiografiska Sallskapets i Lund Forhandlingar 17: 90 - 106." type="journal article" year="1947">Carlgren 1947</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Since then, the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FE60D1858A63FB48" authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1947" box="[450,590,1207,1231]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE60D1858A63FB48" box="[450,590,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Metedwardsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been revised due to a lack of new specimens. Based on the current re-description of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEECD1CA8A07FA97" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[334,554,1272,1296]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FEECD1CA8A07FA97" box="[334,554,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Metedwardsia akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resulting from thorough examination of the characteristics of newly collected topotypic specimens, revision of this diagnosis is required. As the cnidom of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEFFD06889E6FAF6" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[349,459,1369,1393]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FEFFD06889E6FAF6" box="[349,459,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">M. akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never had been formally described, we have added a description of the cnidom to the diagnosis. The microcnemes extending from the oral to the aboral end are found only in this genus among the 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FD05D08988F5FA74" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
, suborder 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEEED0E989C6FA74" box="[332,491,1499,1523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" rank="subOrder" subOrder="Anenthemonae">Anenthemonae</taxonomicName>
. The 16 microcnemes are easily distinguishable from the eight macrocnemes by their smaller size, absence of retractor muscles, and the trilobated filament and gonad, and they are elongated from the distal to proximal end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C24036A1E97D4541FF17D34C8D57FD60" blockId="3.[156,768,523,2077]" lastBlockId="3.[820,1432,198,743]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
Although this genus has been included in 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FDDAD34C8AD2F911" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" box="[632,767,1662,1686]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
for several decades, but there are some different opinions. 
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FF3ED38D895BF950" author="Gusmao, L. C. &amp; Brandao, L. A. &amp; Daly, M." box="[156,374,1727,1751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" refId="ref5835" refString="Gusmao, L. C., Brandao, L. A., and Daly, M. 2016. Edwardsia migottoi sp. nov., the first sea anemone species of Edwardsia de Quatrefages 1842 (Anthozoa: Actiniaria: Edwardsiidae) from the southwestern Atlantic. Marine Biodiversity doi 10.1007 / s 12526 - 016 - 0585 - z." type="book" year="2016">
Gusmão 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FF5BD3F28900F950" box="[249,301,1727,1751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
recently suggested placing 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FD30D3F28AD2F950" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[658,767,1727,1751]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FD30D3F28AD2F950" box="[658,767,1727,1751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">M. akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FF7DD3D28948F97F" authorityName="Andres" authorityYear="1883" box="[223,357,1760,1784]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Halcampidae</taxonomicName>
, a family belonging to the different suborder, 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FF7FD2328973F89F" box="[221,350,1792,1816]" class="Anthozoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="subOrder" subOrder="Enthemonae">Enthemonae</taxonomicName>
, because 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FE19D2328A68F89F" authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1947" box="[443,581,1792,1816]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FE19D2328A68F89F" box="[443,581,1792,1816]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Metedwardsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have microcnemes but rather imperfect mesenteries extended along the entire body in which muscles develop, whereas the microcnemes in other 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FEC7D25089C1F8FD" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" box="[357,492,1890,1914]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
genera are restricted to the distal-most column and have poorly developed musculature, which features rather resembles 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FE45D2918A46F83C" authorityName="Andres" authorityYear="1883" box="[487,619,1955,1979]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Halcampidae</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FD0AD29188F5F85C" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
. However, their taxonomic conclusion was based only on the reference citation of the morphological characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FF14DD37890CF79B" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[182,289,2052,2076]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FF14DD37890CF79B" box="[182,289,2052,2076]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">M. akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Contrary, a molecular phylogenetic tree developed by 
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FC2DD5F48C85FF59" author="Rodriguez, E. &amp; Daly, M." box="[911,1192,198,222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="10958" refId="ref6277" refString="Rodriguez, E. and Daly, M. 2010. Phylogenetic relationships among deep-sea and chemosynthetic sea anemones: Actinoscyphiidae and Actinostolidae (Actiniaria: Mesomyaria). PLoS One 5: e 10958." type="journal article" year="2010">Rodríguez and Daly (2010)</bibRefCitation>
assigned 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FAACD5F58D57FF59" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[1294,1402,198,222]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FAACD5F58D57FF59" box="[1294,1402,198,222]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">M. akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FCFDD5D58BEAFF78" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[863,967,231,255]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actiniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Actiniidae</taxonomicName>
subclade within the Endomyaria clade. Actiniid sea anemones belong to the farther clade from 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FAC8D4358BBAFEC7" authorityName="Andres" authorityYear="1883" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Halcampidae</taxonomicName>
: this two families are different in superfamily level (
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FC99D47A8C37FEE7" author="Rodriguez, E. &amp; Barbeitos, M. S. &amp; Brugler, M. R. &amp; Crowley, L. M. &amp; Grajales, A. &amp; Gusmao, L. &amp; Haussermann, V. &amp; Reft, A. &amp; Daly, M." box="[827,1050,328,352]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="96998" refId="ref6189" refString="Rodriguez, E., Barbeitos, M. S., Brugler, M. R., Crowley, L. M., Grajales, A., Gusmao, L., Haussermann, V., Reft, A., and Daly, M. 2014. Hidden among sea anemones: The first comprehensive phylogenetic reconstruction of the order Actiniaria (Cnidaria, Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) reveals a novel group of hexacorals. PLoS One 9: e 96998." type="journal article" year="2014">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FC0ED47B8BF2FEE7" box="[940,991,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Accordingly, based on this phylogenetic tree, 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FC02D45B8C05FE06" authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1947" box="[928,1064,361,385]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FC02D45B8C05FE06" box="[928,1064,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Metedwardsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is strongly related to 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FAF3D45B8B72FE26" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" class="Anthozoa" family="Actiniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Actiniidae</taxonomicName>
, should not be accommodated to 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FB0FD4BB8D1FFE26" authorityName="Andres" authorityYear="1883" box="[1197,1330,393,417]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Halcampidae</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FC96D4988C69FE45" author="Rodriguez, E. &amp; Daly, M." box="[820,1092,426,450]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="10958" refId="ref6277" refString="Rodriguez, E. and Daly, M. 2010. Phylogenetic relationships among deep-sea and chemosynthetic sea anemones: Actinoscyphiidae and Actinostolidae (Actiniaria: Mesomyaria). PLoS One 5: e 10958." type="journal article" year="2010">Rodríguez and Daly (2010)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide detailed information about the morphological features of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FB47D4F98D7FFE65" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[1253,1362,458,482]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FB47D4F98D7FFE65" box="[1253,1362,458,482]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">M. akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen on which their phylogenetic analysis was based. Therefore, it is still possible that the molecular data of 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FAB6D73E8D50FDA4" authorityName="Bay and Lake Akkeshi. Uchida" authorityYear="1940" box="[1300,1405,523,547]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="akkeshi">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FAB6D73E8D50FDA4" box="[1300,1405,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">M. akkeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="A66E4B50E97D4541FC96D71E8C61FDC3" author="Rodriguez, E. &amp; Daly, M." box="[820,1100,556,580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" pagination="10958" refId="ref6277" refString="Rodriguez, E. and Daly, M. 2010. Phylogenetic relationships among deep-sea and chemosynthetic sea anemones: Actinoscyphiidae and Actinostolidae (Actiniaria: Mesomyaria). PLoS One 5: e 10958." type="journal article" year="2010">Rodríguez and Daly (2010)</bibRefCitation>
might be based on a misidentified, or wrong specimen. As such, we concluded 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FA80D77E8B62FD02" authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1947" class="Anthozoa" family="Halcampidae" genus="Metedwardsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FA80D77E8B62FD02" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Metedwardsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be remained within the 
<taxonomicName id="05FF4D22E97D4541FB31D75F8D35FD02" authorityName="Andress" authorityYear="1881" box="[1171,1304,621,645]" class="Anthozoa" family="Edwardsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Edwardsiidae</taxonomicName>
for the time being (Izumi 
<emphasis id="F08BEAB3E97D4541FC65D7BC8BD0FD22" box="[967,1021,653,677]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">et al.</emphasis>
2018); molecular analysis of topotypic specimens is urgently needed in order to clarify the incontrovertible taxonomic and phylogenetic position of this genus.
</paragraph>
